Crude oil production from Norway's offshore fields averaged 1,545,000 barrels a day in August, compared with the previous August's 1,015,000, according to figures released Friday. 

Total production of oil, natural gas and condensate was 8.6 million tons of oil equivalent in August 1989, compared with 6.4 million tons a year earlier, the Norwegian Petroleum Directorate said. 

